[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods/main/G1R/LockpickSettings/nexus-page/images/section-features.png[/img]

[size=4][b]More Tries[/b][/size]
[color=#ffffff]Lockpick durability rises +10 (by default) over the vanilla value of your lockpicking skill.[/color]
[line]
[b][size=4]Next-Move Hint [/size][/b][i](F7, off by default)[/i] 
The piece to move next lights up: [b][color=#00ff00]GREEN [/color][/b]to turn it [b][color=#00ff00]LEFT[/color] [/b]and [b][color=#1e84cc]BLUE [/color][/b]to turn it [color=#1e84cc][b]RIGHT[/b][/color]. 
[line]
[b][size=4]Connection Display[/size] [/b][i](F8, off by default)[/i] 
Connections to your selected piece will be highlighted: [color=#9900ff][b]PURPLE[/b] [/color]moves the [color=#9900ff]SAME DIRECTION[/color] and [b][color=#980000]RED [/color][/b]moves [color=#980000]OPPOSITE DIRECTION[/color].


[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods/main/G1R/LockpickSettings/nexus-page/images/section-requirements.png[/img]

[url=https://github.com/UE4SS-RE/RE-UE4SS/releases/tag/experimental-latest]UE4SS, experimental build[/url]. 
The game runs Unreal Engine 5.4.3, newer than the stable 3.0.1 release, so grab [b]experimental-latest[/b] (the regular zip, not the zDEV package).


[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods/main/G1R/LockpickSettings/nexus-page/images/section-install.png[/img]

[list=1]
[*]Extract the UE4SS zip into [b]...\Gothic 1 Remake\G1R\Binaries\Win64[/b], so dwmapi.dll sits next to G1R-Win64-Shipping.exe and a ue4ss folder appears beside it.[/*]
[*]Extract the LockpickSettings zip from this page into [b]...\Win64\ue4ss\Mods[/b]:
[code]...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\enabled.txt
...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\Scripts\  (main.lua, config.lua, feature folders)
...\ue4ss\Mods\LockpickSettings\shared\    (bundled helper library)[/code]
The bundled enabled.txt activates the mod. You do not need to edit mods.txt.[/*]
[*]Start the game. [b]...\ue4ss\UE4SS.log[/b] should show something like:
[code][LockpickSettings] Loaded 2.7.8-alpha (kit 1.0.0) [...][/code]
[/*]
[/list]


[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods/main/G1R/LockpickSettings/nexus-page/images/section-config.png[/img]

Edit [b]Scripts\config.lua[/b], apply with a game restart.

[list]
[*][b]extraTries[/b]: bonus on top of the vanilla tries (default 10)[/*]
[*][b]showNextMove[/b] / [b]showConnections[/b]: whether each assist is active at startup (default false)[/*]
[*][b]nextMoveHotkey[/b] / [b]connectionsHotkey[/b]: the toggle keys (default "F7" / "F8", "" disables)[/*]
[*][b]hintColorLeft[/b] / [b]hintColorRight[/b]: hint colors as {r, g, b}, encoding the turn (set both equal for a directionless hint)[/*]
[*][b]partnerColorSame[/b] / [b]partnerColorOpposite[/b]: connection colors as {r, g, b}[/*]
[*][b]debugSolver[/b]: verbose solver log for bug reports. On by default during the alpha; set false for quiet play.[/*]
[/list]


[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods/main/G1R/LockpickSettings/nexus-page/images/section-safety.png[/img]

[list]
[*]No game files are modified, nothing is patched on disk. Pure UE4SS Lua.[/*]
[*]The tries boost is idempotent: already-raised values are recognized and never stack across sessions, saves or reloads.[/*]
[*]The assists read only. Your inputs reach the game untouched, and the hint computes in tiny per-tick slices so the game never stalls.[/*]
[/list]


[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Tautellini/TautelliniMods/main/G1R/LockpickSettings/nexus-page/images/section-troubleshooting.png[/img]

[list]
[*][b]No [LockpickSettings] lines in UE4SS.log:[/b] the folder layout is wrong; enabled.txt must sit directly inside the LockpickSettings folder, exactly as shown under Installation.[/*]
[*][b]"durability X not a known tier":[/b] a game patch changed the vanilla values; update boost.BASE_TRIES in Scripts/tries/boost.lua.[/*]
[*][b]"No graph data for lock":[/b] that lock is not in the shipped data (one lock in the game has none); the hint stays off for it, everything else works.[/*]
[*][b]Access violation when quitting:[/b] known cosmetic UE4SS teardown issue, after everything is saved. Harmless.[/*]
[/list]


